In heterosexual adults, sexually transmitted diseases that occur frequently are chlamydia infections, trichomonas, candidiasis (fungus), gonorrhea, and human papillomaviruses.
HIV is relatively low among heterosexual adults, but about 20 percent of newly infected people belong to this group.
Among adolescents, chlamydia infections occur significantly more frequently than in other groups of the population.
